# Package Management & Build Tools

## Bun Usage
- **ALWAYS** use `bun` for all package management and script execution
- Install packages: `bun add package-name`
- Install dev dependencies: `bun add -d package-name`
- Run scripts: `bun run script-name`
- Execute commands: `bun dlx command`

## Examples
```bash
# Installing packages
bun add react-hook-form zod
bun add -d @types/node

# Running scripts
bun run dev
bun run build

# Using dlx for one-time commands
bun dlx shadcn@latest add button
```

## Never Use
- Do not use `npm`, `yarn`, or `pnpm`
- Always prefer `bun` commands in all scenarios
